{
  "texts": [
    "The Weissenberg number (Wi) is used to compare the elastic forces to the viscous forces.",
    "Reported Weissenberg numbers range from 0.02 to 0.8 at different feeding rates (Pigeonneau et al., 2020; Marion et al., 2023), which are relatively low.",
    "Nevertheless, because the polymer melt within the nozzle is dominated by elongational flow, viscoelastic models remain more suitable for accurately capturing the flow behavior.",
    "With respect to the pressure loss, it can be observed that most losses occur within the nozzle since the losses through the liquefier are usually insignificant due to its larger diameter (Phan et al., 2020).",
    "When GNF and viscoelastic models were compared, the viscoelastic model was shown to be more accurate in predicting the pressure drop in the nozzle and the feeding force (Serdeczny et al., 2022)."
  ]
}